Use the contrast provided by the red and black face paints over the white base to create noticeable and fun details. Using your windpipe, lower lip and chin as guides, you can trace black lines on your lower face. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/92/Dress-As-an-Evil-Wizard-for-Halloween-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Dress-As-an-Evil-Wizard-for-Halloween-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/92/Dress-As-an-Evil-Wizard-for-Halloween-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Dress-As-an-Evil-Wizard-for-Halloween-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
