You might choose to make your lips blood red and to create blood trails running from your mouth and eyes. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/83/Dress-As-an-Evil-Wizard-for-Halloween-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Dress-As-an-Evil-Wizard-for-Halloween-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/83/Dress-As-an-Evil-Wizard-for-Halloween-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Dress-As-an-Evil-Wizard-for-Halloween-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

You can also add a bloody ankh to your forehead. (The ankh is meant as a kind of symbolic irony. It is an Egyptian symbol of life and the fact that it is written in blood on an evil wizard’s face adds to the creepiness of the costume. ){"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bb/Dress-As-an-Evil-Wizard-for-Halloween-Step-8Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Dress-As-an-Evil-Wizard-for-Halloween-Step-8Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bb/Dress-As-an-Evil-Wizard-for-Halloween-Step-8Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Dress-As-an-Evil-Wizard-for-Halloween-Step-8Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
